    "The generator model employs the ReLU activation as described by Nair et al. [66], with the exception of the convolutional layers, which makes use of the Tanh activation.",
    "It has been analyzed in research that when the model was given a bounded activation, it quickly learned to maximize the training distribution.",
    "Balance between generator and discriminatorIt is common for there to be an imbalance between the generators and the discriminator, that might trigger mode collapse and non-convergence.",
    "The obvious solution is to give them more variety in their training, which will prevent them from being over fit.",
    "Although the researchers have made very little advancement, very few of them believe that this is not a workable or acceptable solution due to the fact that a good discriminator produces a highquality result [67]."
